@startuml
title RSS Lambda - Control Flow Sequence Diagram

participant "CloudWatch Event\n(Schedule)" as CWE
participant "rsscrawl\nLambda" as Crawl
participant "S3 Bucket" as S3
participant "feeds.txt" as Feeds
participant "Step Function\n(rssblog)" as SF
participant "rssgetfeed\nLambda" as GetFeed
participant "RSS Feed\nSource" as RSS
participant "readability-lxml\nLibrary" as ReadLib
participant "AWS Comprehend" as Comprehend
participant "DynamoDB\nTable" as DDB
participant "SES" as SES
participant "Algolia\nSearch Index" as Algolia
participant "AppSync\nGraphQL API" as AppSync
participant "Client" as Client
participant "pagecount\nLambda" as PageCount

== RSS Feed Monitoring and Processing ==

CWE -> Crawl: Trigger (scheduled)
activate Crawl

Crawl -> S3: Check existing data
activate S3
S3 --> Crawl: Return existing data
deactivate S3

Crawl -> Feeds: Retrieve RSS feed URLs
activate Feeds
Feeds --> Crawl: Feed URL list
deactivate Feeds

Crawl -> SF: Start execution\n(feed URLs)
activate SF
deactivate Crawl

SF -> SF: Map state (fan-out)\nfor each feed URL

loop For each RSS feed URL
    SF -> GetFeed: Invoke\n(feed URL)
    activate GetFeed

    GetFeed -> RSS: HTTP GET RSS feed
    activate RSS
    RSS --> GetFeed: RSS XML content
    deactivate RSS

    GetFeed -> GetFeed: Parse RSS feed\n(feedparser)

    loop For each blog post in feed
        GetFeed -> GetFeed: Extract metadata\n(title, link, date)

        GetFeed -> GetFeed: Fetch blog post URL

        GetFeed -> ReadLib: Extract main content\nfrom HTML
        activate ReadLib
        ReadLib --> GetFeed: Clean text content
        deactivate ReadLib

        GetFeed -> Comprehend: Entity recognition\non content
        activate Comprehend
        Comprehend --> GetFeed: Entities and tags
        deactivate Comprehend

        GetFeed -> DDB: PutItem\n(blog post data)
        activate DDB
        DDB --> GetFeed: Success
        deactivate DDB

        alt SendEmails = true
            GetFeed -> SES: Send email notification\n(new post alert)
            activate SES
            SES --> GetFeed: Email sent
            deactivate SES
        end

        alt EnableAlgolia = true
            GetFeed -> Algolia: Index blog post\n(search data)
            activate Algolia
            Algolia --> GetFeed: Indexed successfully
            deactivate Algolia
        end
    end

    GetFeed --> SF: Processing complete\nfor feed
    deactivate GetFeed
end

SF -> SF: Fan-in results\nfrom all feeds

alt StorePublicS3 = true
    SF -> S3: PutObject\n(public JSON file)
    activate S3
    S3 --> SF: Stored successfully
    deactivate S3
end

SF --> CWE: Execution complete
deactivate SF

== Data Access via AppSync (Optional) ==

alt CreateAppSync = true
    Client -> AppSync: GraphQL query\n(read blog posts)
    activate Client
    activate AppSync

    AppSync -> AppSync: Execute VTL resolver

    AppSync -> DDB: Query/Scan\n(blog posts)
    activate DDB
    DDB --> AppSync: Blog post data
    deactivate DDB

    AppSync --> Client: GraphQL response\n(blog posts)
    deactivate AppSync
    deactivate Client
end

== Manual Article Count Tracking ==

note right of PageCount
Manual invocation only
end note

CWE -> PageCount: Manual invoke
activate PageCount

PageCount -> DDB: Scan table\n(all blogs)
activate DDB
DDB --> PageCount: All blog data
deactivate DDB

PageCount -> PageCount: Calculate article counts\nper blog source

PageCount -> DDB: UpdateItem\n(store counts)
activate DDB
DDB --> PageCount: Success
deactivate DDB

PageCount --> CWE: Complete
deactivate PageCount

@enduml
